params._proposalId: The ID of the proposal to be checked.

returns._0: True if the proposal can be executed, false otherwise.

canVeto(uint256,address).details: The function assumes that the queried proposal exists.

params._account: The account address to be checked.

returns._0: Returns true if the account is allowed to veto.

params._actions: The actions that will be executed after the proposal passes.
params._allowFailureMap: Allows proposal to succeed even if an action reverts. Uses bitmap representation. If the bit at index `x` is 1, the tx succeeds even if the action at `x` failed. Passing 0 will be treated as atomic execution.
params._duration: The amount of seconds to allow for token holders to veto. NOTE: If the supplied value is zero, the proposal will be treated as an emergency one.

effectiveVotingPower(uint256,bool).details: This assumes that the Taiko Bridge is delegating to itself.

params._isL2Available: Whether the L2 can be part of the voting power or not.

params._proposalId: The ID of the proposal to be executed.

returns.actions: The actions to be executed in the associated DAO after the proposal has passed.
returns.allowFailureMap: The bit map representations of which actions are allowed to revert so tx still succeeds.
returns.executed: Whether the proposal is executed or not.
returns.metadataURI: The IPFS URI at which the metadata is pinned.
returns.open: Whether the proposal is open or not.
returns.parameters: The parameters of the proposal vote.
returns.vetoTally: The current voting power used to veto the proposal.

params._account: The account address to be checked.

returns._0: The whether the given account has vetoed the given proposal.

params._dao: The IDAO interface of the associated DAO.
params._taikoBridge: The address of the contract that can bridge voting vetoes back.
params._taikoL1: The address of the contract where the protocol status can be checked.

isMember(address).details: This function must be implemented in the plugin contract that introduces the members to the DAO.

params._account: The address of the account to be checked.

returns._0: Whether the account is a member or not.
Returns `true` if the total veto power against the proposal is greater or equal than the threshold and `false` otherwise.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

returns._0: Returns `true` if the interface is supported.

upgradeTo(address).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

PROPOSER_PERMISSION_ID().notice: The ID of the permission required to create a proposal.

UPDATE_OPTIMISTIC_GOVERNANCE_SETTINGS_PE.notice: The ID of the permission required to call the `updateOptimisticGovernanceSettings` function.

UPGRADE_PLUGIN_PERMISSION_ID().notice: The ID of the permission required to call the `_authorizeUpgrade` function.

bridgedVotingPower(uint256).notice: Returns the total voting power bridged to the L2 at the given timestamp.

canExecute(uint256).notice: Checks if a proposal can be executed.

canVeto(uint256,address).notice: Checks if an account can participate on an optimistic proposal. This can be because the proposal - has not started, - has ended, - was executed, or - the voter doesn't have voting power.

constructor.notice: Disables the initializers on the implementation contract to prevent it from being left uninitialized.

effectiveVotingPower(uint256,bool).notice: Returns the effective voting power that can vote at the given timestamp.

getProposal(uint256).notice: Returns all information for a proposal vote by its ID.

governanceSettings().notice: The struct storing the governance settings.

hasVetoed(uint256,address).notice: Returns whether the account has voted for the proposal.  Note, that this does not check if the account has vetoing power.

implementation().notice: Returns the address of the implementation contract in the [proxy storage slot](https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-1967) slot the [UUPS proxy](https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-1822) is pointing to.

initialize(address,(uint32,uint32,uint32.notice: Initializes the component to be used by inheriting contracts.

isL2Available().notice: Determines whether L2 votes are currently usable for voting

isMember(address).notice: Checks if an account is a member of the DAO.

isMinVetoRatioReached(uint256).notice: Checks if the total votes against a proposal is greater than the veto threshold.

minVetoRatio().notice: Returns the veto ratio parameter stored in the optimistic governance settings.

parseProposalId(uint256).notice: Splits the components behind the given proposal ID

proposalCount().notice: Returns the proposal count determining the next proposal ID.

proposalIds(uint256).notice: A mapping to enumerate proposal ID's by index

supportsInterface(bytes4).notice: Checks if this or the parent contract supports an interface by its ID.

taikoBridge().notice: The address of the L2 token bridge, to determine the L2 balance bridged to the L2 on proposal creation.

taikoL1().notice: Taiko L1 contract to check the status from.

totalVotingPower(uint256).notice: Returns the total voting power checkpointed for a specific timestamp.

veto(uint256).notice: Registers the veto for the given proposal.

votingToken().notice: An [OpenZeppelin `Votes`](https://docs.openzeppelin.com/contracts/4.x/api/governance#Votes) compatible contract referencing the token being used for voting.
